{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"nEyPyFz9bSSGpEVrVHtjc","title":"Mechanism Design","desc":"","updated":1641849840872,"created":1641835484741,"custom":{},"fname":"science.math.Game Theory.Mechanism Design","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"ed9ba82b86fca73c5ff6f7109b655196","links":[{"from":{"fname":"science.math.Game Theory.Algorithmic Game Theory","id":"u9ezB2wPVoCE3ISScd8cX","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":450},"end":{"line":15,"column":46,"offset":495},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Game Theory.Mechanism Design"}],"anchors":{},"children":[],"parent":"tcyygtOru8BzktKFRQ2Wy","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"mechanism-design\">Mechanism Design<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#mechanism-design\"></a></h1>\n<p>from <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechanism_design\">wikipedia</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/assets/images/2022-01-10-18-27-43.png\" alt=\"Mechanism Design Diagram\">\nThe Stanley Reiter diagram above illustrates a game of mechanism design. The upper-left space <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Θ</span></span></span></span></span>  depicts the type space and the upper-right space <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span> the space of outcomes. The social choice function <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f(\\theta )</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> maps a type profile to an outcome. In games of mechanism design, agents send messages <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span></span> in a game environment <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">g</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span></span></span></span></span>. The equilibrium in the game <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ξ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>M</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>g</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\xi (M,g,\\theta )</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04601em;\">ξ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> can be designed to implement some social choice function <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f(\\theta )</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/u9ezB2wPV